{"type":"log","step_name":"update-docs","message":"I understand the bug. The default `bufio.Scanner` buffer is 64KB, but Claude Code can produce JSON log lines exceeding that. When a line is too large, the scanner silently stops, dropping all subsequent log entries. The fix increases the buffer to 1MB in both `server.go` (gRPC tracking) and `handler.go` (web streaming).","timestamp":"2026-03-11T21:00:29.647707583Z"}
